headline: The Boeing strike is over. But the effects will be felt for a while
summary: The nearly two-month-long machinists’ strike at Boeing (BA) had a big immediate effect on both the planemaker’s bottom line and the economy at large, but the work stoppage will have a long-tail ripple effect. The research firm Oxford Economics noted that aviation manufacturing was a big reason for the 0.1% advance in industrial output that was lower than market expectations.
